The '''Valea Nucarilor Wind Farm''' is a wind power project in [[Valea Nucarilor]], [[Tulcea County]], [[Romania]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Enel inaugurates 70 MW wind park in Tulcea|url=http://business-review.eu/featured/enel-inaugurates-70-mw-wind-park-in-tulcea-2/|accessdate=6 November 2013|newspaper=Business Review|date=June 26, 2012}}</ref>  It has 80 individual [[wind turbine]]s<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businessmagazin.ro/analize/energie/dobrogea-raiul-energiei-eoliene-2307910/?p=1|title=Dobrogea, raiul energiei eoliene|date=2007-12-16|publisher=''Business Magazin''|language=Romanian|accessdate=2009-08-24}}</ref> with a nominal output of around 0.75 [[Watt#Megawatt|MW]] which will deliver up to 70 MW of power, enough to power over 36,000 homes, with a capital investment required of approximately US$75 million.

