{{Infobox power station | name = Yttre Stengrund | name_official = Yttre Stengrund offshore wind farm | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = Sweden | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = Location of Yttre Stengrund | coordinates = {{coord|56.166423|16.017246|region:SW_scale:50000|display=inline,title}} | coordinates_ref = | country = [[Sweden]] | location = | status = D | construction_began = | commissioned = {{Start date|2001}} | decommissioned = {{End date|2015|11}} | cost = | owner = | operator = [[Vattenfall]] | ps_units_manu_model = [[NEG Micon]] 2&nbsp;MW | ps_units_decommissioned = 5 x 2&nbsp;MW | wind_hub_height = | wind_rotor_diameter = | wind_rated_speed = | wind_farm_type = Offshore | wind_site_area = | ps_electrical_capacity = 10 | ps_electrical_cap_fac = | website = | extra = }}
'''Yttre Stengrund''' was an offshore wind farm in [[Sweden]], operated by [[Vattenfall]]. The wind farm was commissioned in 2001, using five 2 MW [[NEG Micon]] turbines. All turbines in Yttre Stengrund were decommissioned by November 2015,<ref>{{cite web|title=THE END IS NEAR FOR YTTRE STENGRUND|url= http://news.vattenfall.com/en/article/end-near-yttre-stengrund |website=NEWS FROM VATTENFALL|publisher=Vattenfall|accessdate=25 October 2016|date=11 November 2015}}</ref> becoming the first offshore wind farm to be decommissioned in the world.<ref>{{cite news|title=Vattenfall to scrap Yttre Stengrund|url= http://renews.biz/75899/vattenfall-to-scrap-yttre-stengrund/ |accessdate=25 October 2016|work=reNEWS - Renewable Energy News|date=18 September 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.offshorewind.biz/2016/01/25/vattenfall-wraps-up-first-ever-offshore-wind-farm-decommissioning/ |title=Vattenfall Wraps Up First Ever Offshore Wind Farm Decommissioning|publisher= |accessdate=20 April 2017}}</ref>
